<%# views/privacy-policy.ejs %>
<%- include('partials/header', {
    pageTitle: 'Privacy Policy - Vanier Capital',
    pageDescription: 'Vanier Capital Privacy Policy governing the collection, use, and protection of investor and visitor data.',
    path: '/privacy-policy'
}) %>

<section class="pt-24 md:pt-32 pb-10 md:pb-16 px-6 md:px-16 bg-[#0f2e22] text-white">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
        <span class="font-sans text-sm font-bold text-white/60 uppercase tracking-widest block mb-4">Legal</span>
        <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl text-white tracking-tight mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="font-sans text-sm text-white/50 uppercase tracking-widest">Effective Date: <%= typeof lastUpdated !== 'undefined' ? lastUpdated : 'March 9, 2026' %></p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-16 py-12 md:py-20">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-16">
        <article class="lg:col-span-8 space-y-12" id="legal-main">

            <div>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Vanier Capital, LLC ("Vanier Capital," "the Firm," "we," "us," or "our") is committed to safeguarding the privacy and security of all personal information entrusted to us by visitors, prospective investors, limited partners, and other users of this website (vaniercapital.com, the "Site"). This Privacy Policy describes our practices concerning the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of personal data.</p>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">By accessing or using this Site, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree, you should discontinue use of the Site immediately.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-[#0f2e22] mb-6">Information We Collect</h2>
                <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Personal Data</h3>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">In the course of your interaction with the Firm, whether through inquiry forms, investor applications, or direct correspondence, we may collect personally identifiable information including but not limited to:</p>
                <ul class="space-y-2 border-l-2 border-[#0f2e22] pl-6 mb-6">
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">Full legal name</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">Email address and telephone number</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">Entity name, title, and professional affiliation</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">Accreditation status and investor classification</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">Capital commitment and investment interest details</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">Geographic location (city/state)</li>
                </ul>
                <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Usage &amp; Technical Data</h3>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">We automatically collect certain technical information when you visit the Site, including IP address, browser type and version, operating system, referring URLs, pages visited, time and duration of visits, and unique device identifiers. This data is collected through server logs and, where applicable, analytics tools.</p>
                <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Cookies &amp; Tracking Technologies</h3>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">We use strictly necessary cookies to operate the Site (session management, CSRF protection, authentication). We may also employ analytics cookies to understand aggregate usage patterns. You may configure your browser to reject cookies; however, certain Site functionality may be impaired.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-[#0f2e22] mb-6">How We Use Your Information</h2>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The Firm uses collected information exclusively for legitimate business purposes:</p>
                <ul class="space-y-2 border-l-2 border-[#0f2e22] pl-6">
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">To evaluate and process investor applications and capital commitments</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">To communicate with prospective and existing limited partners regarding fund matters</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">To respond to inquiries, requests, and correspondence</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">To maintain and secure the Site and our technology infrastructure</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">To comply with applicable legal and regulatory obligations</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">To analyze aggregate, anonymized usage data for the purpose of improving the Site</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-[#0f2e22] mb-6">Data Sharing &amp; Disclosure</h2>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Vanier Capital does not sell, rent, or trade your personal information. We may share data only in the following limited circumstances:</p>
                <ul class="space-y-2 border-l-2 border-[#0f2e22] pl-6">
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]"><strong>Service Providers:</strong> Trusted third-party vendors who assist in Site hosting, email delivery, analytics, and data storage, bound by contractual confidentiality obligations</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]"><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> When required by law, subpoena, court order, or regulatory authority</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]"><strong>Protection of Rights:</strong> To protect the rights, property, or safety of Vanier Capital, its partners, or the public</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]"><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In connection with any merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, where data may be transferred as part of the transaction</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-[#0f2e22] mb-6">Investor Data Protection</h2>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">We recognize the heightened sensitivity of financial and investment-related data. All investor information, including capital account data, subscription documents, K-1 statements, and fund correspondence accessible through our LP Portal, is subject to enhanced security measures including:</p>
                <ul class="space-y-2 border-l-2 border-[#0f2e22] pl-6">
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">Encryption in transit (TLS/SSL) and at rest</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">Role-based access controls restricting data to authorized personnel</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">Authentication-gated portals for investor-specific information</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">Regular security audits and vulnerability assessments</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-[#0f2e22] mb-6">Data Retention</h2>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">We retain personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes described in this Policy, satisfy legal and regulatory retention requirements, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements. Investor records may be retained for the duration of the fund lifecycle and such additional periods as required by applicable tax and securities regulations. When data is no longer required, it is securely deleted or irreversibly anonymized.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-[#0f2e22] mb-6">Your Rights</h2>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights regarding your personal data, including:</p>
                <ul class="space-y-2 border-l-2 border-[#0f2e22] pl-6 mb-4">
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">Right of access to the data we hold about you</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">Right to correction of inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">Right to deletion, subject to legal retention requirements</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">Right to restrict or object to processing</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]">Right to data portability where technically feasible</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at <a href="mailto:info@vaniercapital.com" class="text-[#0f2e22] font-bold hover:underline">info@vaniercapital.com</a>. We may require identity verification prior to processing your request.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-[#0f2e22] mb-6">Legal Bases for Processing (EEA/UK)</h2>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">If you are located in the European Economic Area or the United Kingdom, we process personal data under the following legal bases:</p>
                <ul class="space-y-2 border-l-2 border-[#0f2e22] pl-6">
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]"><strong>Contract:</strong> To provide services you have requested or to take pre-contractual steps at your request</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]"><strong>Legitimate Interests:</strong> To secure and improve the Site, prevent misuse, and understand usage patterns</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]"><strong>Consent:</strong> Where specifically required; you may withdraw consent at any time</li>
                    <li class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a]"><strong>Legal Obligation:</strong> To comply with applicable laws and regulatory requirements</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-[#0f2e22] mb-6">International Data Transfers</h2>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Your information may be transferred to, stored, and processed in the United States, where our servers and operations are located. If you are accessing this Site from outside the United States, please be aware that data protection laws may differ from those in your jurisdiction. By continuing to use the Site, you consent to the transfer and processing of your data in the United States in accordance with this Policy.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-[#0f2e22] mb-6">Third-Party Links</h2>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">This Site may contain links to third-party websites. Vanier Capital is not responsible for the privacy practices or content of those sites. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party site you visit.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-[#0f2e22] mb-6">Children's Privacy</h2>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">This Site is not directed at individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from minors. If we become aware that we have inadvertently collected data from a minor, we will take prompt steps to delete it.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-[#0f2e22] mb-6">Changes to This Policy</h2>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or applicable law. The revised policy will be posted on this page with an updated effective date. Your continued use of the Site after such changes constitutes acceptance of the revised Policy.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-t border-[#0f2e22]/20 pt-12" id="contact-us">
                <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-[#0f2e22] mb-6">Contact</h2>
                <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">For questions regarding this Privacy Policy or to exercise your data rights, contact:</p>
                <div class="border-l-2 border-[#0f2e22] pl-6">
                    <p class="font-sans text-sm text-[#1a1a1a] font-bold">Vanier Capital, LLC</p>
                    <p class="font-sans text-sm text-gray-700">Email: <a href="mailto:info@vaniercapital.com" class="text-[#0f2e22] font-bold hover:underline">info@vaniercapital.com</a></p>
                </div>
            </div>

        </article>
        <aside class="lg:col-span-4 hidden lg:block" aria-label="Secondary">
            <div class="sticky top-32">
                <div class="font-sans text-xs font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">On This Page</div>
                <nav aria-label="Table of contents">
                    <ul id="legal-toc-list" class="space-y-2 border-l border-[#0f2e22]/20 pl-4"></ul>
                </nav>
            </div>
        </aside>
    </div>
</section>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
